In '''''Ex Parte Dittmarn''''' is an important case in the [[Law of succession in South Africa|South African law of succession]]. The [[testator]]’s [[Will and testament|will]] provided that a farm should be sold by [[public auction]]. A sale was advertised, but the highest [[Bidding|bid]] was not considered high enough to be a true reflection of its [[Value (economics)|value]]. The farm was therefore withdrawn and sold out of hand for a price considerably higher than the bid. The court confirmed this sale to be valid, as sale by public auction would have resulted in serious loss.
