{{Infobox website | name = Internet Theatre Database | logo = | logo_size = | screenshot = | caption = | url = {{URL|theatredb.com}} | type = [[Theater|Theatrical]] [[database]] | registration = Optional | language = [[English language|English]] | owner = Keith Scollick | creator = Keith Scollick | launch_date = {{Start date and age|1999|05}} | revenue = | alexa = {{Decrease}} 6,796,938 ({{as of|2018|10|05|alt=October 2018}})<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/theatredb.com |title=Theatredb.com Traffic, Demographics and Competitors |last= |first= |date= |website= |publisher=[[Alexa Internet]] |access-date=October 5, 2018 |quote=}}</ref> | current_status = Active }} The '''Internet Theatre Database''' ('''ITDb''') is an online database with information about [[Play (theatre)|plays]], [[playwright]]s, [[actor]]s, [[theatre|legitimate theatre]], [[musical theatre]], [[Broadway theatre|Broadway shows]], and similar theatrical information.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=RM&p_theme=rm&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB4E0F7F9D094AA&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|title=Abundant web sites serve theater fans |last=Bornstein|first=Lisa |date=20 August 2000|work=Rocky Mountain News|accessdate=22 August 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/60884065.html?dids=60884065:60884065&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Sep+22%2C+2000&author=DON+SHIRLEY&pub=Los+Angeles+Times&desc=Cybertainment%3B+Mixed+Reviews+for+Theater-Related+Web+Sites&pqatl=google|title=Cybertainment; Mixed Reviews for Theater-Related Web Sites|last=Shirley|first=Don| date=22 September 2000|work=Los Angeles Times - Los Angeles, Calif. |accessdate=23 August 2009}}</ref>
The website is run by several volunteer theatre [[aficionado]]s, each contributing material as time permits. Somewhat similar to the [[Internet Broadway Database]], the site's creators endeavor to include theatre outside of [[New York City]] by indexing [[London]] and [[Off-Broadway]] productions, national tours, and regional theatre. Modelled on the considerably larger [[Internet Movie Database]], the site indexes by six categories: (1) show/play name; (2) people (actor, writer, or director); (3) theatre facility; (4) song title; (5) character/role; and (6) production role. Each day, the site also shows what well-known productions opened or closed on that date at important theatres in the past several decades.
