'''Yojimbo''' is a [[personal information manager]] for [[Mac OS X]] by [[Bare Bones Software]]. It can store notes, images/media, [[Uniform Resource Locator|URL]]s, [[web page]]s. Yojimbo can also encrypt any of its contents and store the password in the [[Apple Keychain|Keychain]]. It is Bare Bones' second [[Cocoa (API)|Cocoa]] application.

==History==
Yojimbo was first released on January 23, 2006. At the time, Bare Bones called it "a completely new information organizer".<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060315044747/http://www.barebones.com/company/press.php?news_id=142 Bare Bones Software Ships New Yojimbo 1.0]</ref>

